      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658224168402-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658224168402-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658224168402-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658224168402-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1658224168402-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half and wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong></p><p>Cut 1 large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>per person and lay the <strong>shredded kale</strong> and <strong>halved green beans</strong> in the middle</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and scrunch the edges up to form a tightly sealed parcel (or two!), then put the parcel[s] on a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until cooked</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1658224170197-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1658224170197-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1658224170197-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1658224170197-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1658224170197-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> to a plate and drizzle <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce</strong> all over them (save the rest for later!), turning the basa several times until the soy sauce has been absorbed</p><p>Sprinkle most of the <strong>cornflour </strong>(reserve 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> for later!) all over and rub it into both sides of the basa until fully coated – this is your <strong>coated basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Coat the fish in the cornflour one side at a time to avoid stickiness!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658224172016-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658224172016-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658224172016-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658224172016-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1658224172016-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until crispy and cooked through – this is your <strong>crispy basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658224175401-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658224175401-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658224175401-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658224175401-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658224175401-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Finely slice half your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and set aside for garnish</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/chilli-and-garlic-1690538132575-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/chilli-and-garlic-1690538132575-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/chilli-and-garlic-1690538132575-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/chilli-and-garlic-1690538132575-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/chilli-and-garlic-1690538132575-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>crispy basa</strong> to a clean plate and set aside</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat and once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger paste</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> and <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and cook for a further 2 min or until the sauce has thickened and becomes sticky – this is your <strong>spicy hoisin sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658224181166-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658224181166-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658224181166-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658224181166-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658224181166-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the greens are done, remove the parcel[s] from the oven and drain away any excess water</p><p>Add them to a bowl with your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then give them a good mix up – these are your <strong>sesame greens</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658224184577-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658224184577-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658224184577-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658224184577-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1658224184577-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy basa</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> and <strong>sesame greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon over the <strong>spicy hoisin sauce</strong> and garnish with the <strong>reserved chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
